Running with a stroller is hard, but use these tips, take a deep breath and clear your head. Make sure your baby is fed before you head out and dressed appropriately, the mornings can be a little chilly as we head into winter If you prefer to let the ‘wheels do the walking’ for you, then a child bike seat will allow you and your most treasured possessions to enjoy everyday bike rides, safely. This is a great way to introduce your children to the joys of biking. If your family prefers a slow and steady pace, then a child carrier backpack is great for low impact walks. * Source: Information supplied by Julia Downey, brand manager of Thule SA’s Active with Kids category; visit thulestore.co.za 